com.skilltradiez.skilltraderz

Class Inventory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.skilltradiez.skilltraderz.Notification
      • com.skilltradiez.skilltraderz.Inventory

  • public class Inventory
extends Notification
    ~~DESCRIPTION: This is going to be the class where we have the inventory and all of it's associated functions that a user will have all clumped together into one coherent object. This object will have a set of attributes that are related to the inventory such as an arraylist of skills. (And that's it.... for now... dun dun dunnnnn!) This object will be method centric, where most of the object will be dealing with manipulating a truckload of functionality throughout the rest of the objects present within the application. An inventory contains the the skills held by a user.

      • commit

        public boolean commit(UserDatabase userDB)
        When invoked will commit to the database all of the changes that have occured since the last commit. Attempts to update the Elastic document for the inventory. If this fails, we get an IO Exception and return false. Signalling failure. If that was successful we move onto invoking the method to save to the local device (As in a flash card in most phones.) the changes to the inventory. If this fails we return false again- indicating failure. If both of those methods go through though we return true to the caller of this method.
        Parameters:
        userDB - UserDatabase Object
        Returns:
        Boolean. True/False.
